buyerAgent.name: Adriana R. Foster, MRP, FMS, CNAS

data.description: You’ll find harmony and balance in this cozy, quiet neighborhood in Heritage Manor. Centrally located in the heart of southside Crestview, it’s just a short drive to the world’s most beautiful gulf beaches and minutes from restaurants, shopping, entertainment, hospitals, military bases and the Interstate. This craftsman home, built by an award-winning homebuilder, offers a spacious, open floor plan featuring nine ft. ceilings, three bedrooms, plus a flex room for an office or fourth bedroom. The kitchen boasts custom cabinetry and is complemented by gorgeous granite countertops and stainless-steel appliances. There is a large center island and a huge pantry. The master suite is a retreat, separated from the guest bedrooms, and features a walk-in closet, garden tub, separate shower and double vanities. The peaceful back yard overlooks lush greenery with a wood deck, privacy fence and sprinkler system. The biggest bonus is the 9 kW solar energy system generating over 10,000-kilowatt hours per year. The power bill for this house is only $12 per month, translating to a huge annual savings for utilities. Schedule your private home tour today.
